One suspect, a now former custodial employee, was arrested at her home without incident on January 7.\n\nThe second suspect, an acquaintance of the custodial employee and a felon with a lengthy criminal history, was rumored to be in the process of fleeing the area for a California destination.\n\nBased on the information concerning the suspect\u2019s possible flight to California, UPD detectives provided a photo of the suspect to Greyhound Bus employees in Bryan. On the morning of Jan. 13, UPD detectives received a phone call from a Greyhound Bus employee advising that the suspect just left their business after trying to buy a bus ticket to Dallas. Knowing he was wanted by our department, one employee stalled their service while another phoned police.
